    "# GamePulse — 02 · Silver Layer\n",
    "## Data Cleaning & Standardization\n",
    "\n",
    "**SYST52461 – Big Data Storage and Analysis**  \n",
    "**Term Project · Winter 2026**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Purpose\n",
    "This notebook reads the four Bronze tables, applies data quality fixes, and writes clean **Silver** Delta tables.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Cleaning Applied\n",
    "| Table | Issues Fixed |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `players` | Standardize `region` + `account_type` to title case; cast `age` to integer; cast `join_date` to date; drop null `email` rows |\n",
    "| `games` | Standardize `genre` + `game_mode` to title case; drop null `game_mode` rows |\n",
    "| `game_sessions` | Cast `session_date` to date; drop rows with `duration_minutes` ≤ 0; impute null `score` with 0 |\n",
    "| `purchases` | Standardize `category` to title case; cast `purchase_date` to date; drop rows with `amount_spent` ≤ 0 |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Environment Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 0,
   "metadata": {
    "application/vnd.databricks.v1+cell": {
     "cellMetadata": {"byteLimit": 2048000, "rowLimit": 10000},
     "inputWidgets": {},
     "nuid": "gp-s-001",
     "showTitle": false,
     "title": ""
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import logging\n",
    "\n",
    "from pyspark.sql import functions as F\n",
    "from pyspark.sql.types import DateType, IntegerType\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Logging ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "logging.basicConfig(\n",
    "    level=logging.INFO,\n",
    "    format=\"%(asctime)s  %(levelname)s  %(message)s\",\n",
    "    datefmt=\"%H:%M:%S\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "log = logging.getLogger(\"gamepulse.silver\")\n",
    "\n",
    "CATALOG = \"sandbox_catalog\"\n",
    "SCHEMA  = \"gamepulse\"\n",
    "\n",
    "log.info(\"Silver notebook ready. Catalog=%s  Schema=%s\", CATALOG, SCHEMA)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Helper Utilities"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 0,
   "metadata": {
    "application/vnd.databricks.v1+cell": {
     "cellMetadata": {"byteLimit": 2048000, "rowLimit": 10000},
     "inputWidgets": {},
     "nuid": "gp-s-002",
     "showTitle": false,
     "title": ""
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def read_table(table_name: str):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Read a Delta table from the active schema.\"\"\"\n",
    "    full_name = f\"{CATALOG}.{SCHEMA}.{table_name}\"\n",
    "    df = spark.read.table(full_name)\n",
    "    log.info(\"Loaded  <- %s  (%d rows)\", full_name, df.count())\n",
    "    return df\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def write_table(df, table_name: str, mode: str = \"overwrite\") -> None:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Write a Spark DataFrame as a Delta table.\"\"\"\n",
    "    full_name = f\"{CATALOG}.{SCHEMA}.{table_name}\"\n",
    "    df.write.format(\"delta\").mode(mode).saveAsTable(full_name)\n",
    "    log.info(\"Written -> %s  (%d rows)\", full_name, df.count())\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def null_report(df, label: str) -> None:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Display null counts per column.\"\"\"\n",
    "    null_counts = df.select([\n",
    "        F.count(F.when(F.col(c).isNull(), c)).alias(c) for c in df.columns\n",
    "    ])\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n── Null Report: {label} ──\")\n",
    "    display(null_counts)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "log.info(\"Helpers defined.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 3. Load Bronze Tables"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 0,
   "metadata": {
    "application/vnd.databricks.v1+cell": {
     "cellMetadata": {"byteLimit": 2048000, "rowLimit": 10000},
     "inputWidgets": {},
     "nuid": "gp-s-003",
     "showTitle": false,
     "title": ""
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "players_raw   = read_table(\"players_bronze\")\n",
    "games_raw     = read_table(\"games_bronze\")\n",
    "sessions_raw  = read_table(\"game_sessions_bronze\")\n",
    "purchases_raw = read_table(\"purchases_bronze\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
{
 "cell_type": "markdown",
 "metadata": {},
 "source": [
  "## Silver Layer Data Cleaning Strategy\n",
  "\n",
  "This layer transforms raw Bronze data into clean and standardized datasets suitable for analysis.\n",
  "\n",
  "Key steps performed:\n",
  "- Handling missing values by dropping or imputing where appropriate\n",
  "- Standardizing categorical fields (e.g., region, account_type)\n",
  "- Converting incorrect data types (e.g., string to integer/date)\n",
  "- Removing invalid records such as negative spending and zero-duration sessions\n",
  "\n",
  "These transformations improve data quality and ensure consistency for downstream analysis in the Gold layer."
 ]
}
    "## 4. Clean `players` → Silver\n",
    "\n",
    "**Steps:**\n",
    "1. Standardize `region` — map all abbreviations/variants to canonical title-case values\n",
    "2. Standardize `account_type` — apply `initcap()` to normalize casing\n",
    "3. Cast `age` from string to integer\n",
    "4. Cast `join_date` from string to date\n",
    "5. Drop rows where `email` is null (required field for player identity)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 0,
   "metadata": {
    "application/vnd.databricks.v1+cell": {
     "cellMetadata": {"byteLimit": 2048000, "rowLimit": 10000},
     "inputWidgets": {},
     "nuid": "gp-s-004",
     "showTitle": false,
     "title": ""
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Step 1: Inspect the raw region and account_type values\n",
    "print(\"Distinct region values (raw):\")\n",
    "display(players_raw.groupBy(\"region\").count().orderBy(\"count\", ascending=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Distinct account_type values (raw):\")\n",
    "display(players_raw.groupBy(\"account_type\").count().orderBy(\"count\", ascending=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 0,
   "metadata": {
    "application/vnd.databricks.v1+cell": {
     "cellMetadata": {"byteLimit": 2048000, "rowLimit": 10000},
     "inputWidgets": {},
     "nuid": "gp-s-005",
     "showTitle": false,
     "title": ""
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Step 2: Map region abbreviations/variants to canonical values\n",
    "region_map = {\n",
    "    \"NA\":             \"North America\",\n",
    "    \"north america\":  \"North America\",\n",
    "    \"EU\":             \"Europe\",\n",
    "    \"europe\":         \"Europe\",\n",
    "    \"APAC\":           \"Asia Pacific\",\n",
    "    \"asia pacific\":   \"Asia Pacific\",\n",
    "    \"LATAM\":          \"Latin America\",\n",
    "    \"latin america\":  \"Latin America\",\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build a CASE WHEN expression from the dictionary\n",
    "region_expr = F.col(\"region\")\n",
    "for raw_val, canonical in region_map.items():\n",
    "    region_expr = F.when(F.col(\"region\") == raw_val, canonical).otherwise(region_expr)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply all cleaning steps in a single chain\n",
    "players_silver = (\n",
    "    players_raw\n",
    "    .withColumn(\"region\",       region_expr)\n",
    "    .withColumn(\"account_type\", F.initcap(F.lower(F.col(\"account_type\"))))  # normalize casing\n",
    "    .withColumn(\"age\",          F.col(\"age\").cast(IntegerType()))            # string → int\n",
    "    .withColumn(\"join_date\",    F.to_date(F.col(\"join_date\"), \"yyyy-MM-dd\")) # string → date\n",
    "    .filter(F.col(\"email\").isNotNull())                                       # drop null emails\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "before = players_raw.count()\n",
    "after  = players_silver.count()\n",
    "print(f\"players: {before} → {after} rows  (dropped {before - after} null-email records)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "null_report(players_silver, \"players_silver\")\n",
    "display(players_silver.limit(10))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 5. Clean `games` → Silver\n",
    "\n",
    "**Steps:**\n",
    "1. Standardize `genre` with `initcap(lower())` — removes all casing variants\n",
    "2. Standardize `game_mode` with `initcap(lower())`\n",
    "3. Drop rows where `game_mode` is null (needed for session-level analysis)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 0,
   "metadata": {
    "application/vnd.databricks.v1+cell": {
     "cellMetadata": {"byteLimit": 2048000, "rowLimit": 10000},
     "inputWidgets": {},
     "nuid": "gp-s-006",
     "showTitle": false,
     "title": ""
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "games_silver = (\n",
    "    games_raw\n",
    "    .withColumn(\"genre\",     F.initcap(F.lower(F.col(\"genre\"))))\n",
    "    .withColumn(\"game_mode\", F.initcap(F.lower(F.col(\"game_mode\"))))\n",
    "    .filter(F.col(\"game_mode\").isNotNull())\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "before = games_raw.count()\n",
    "after  = games_silver.count()\n",
    "print(f\"games: {before} → {after} rows  (dropped {before - after} null-game_mode records)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nDistinct genre values (silver):\")\n",
    "display(games_silver.groupBy(\"genre\").count().orderBy(\"genre\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "display(games_silver)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 6. Clean `game_sessions` → Silver\n",
    "\n",
    "**Steps:**\n",
    "1. Cast `session_date` from string to date\n",
    "2. Drop rows where `duration_minutes` ≤ 0 (invalid sessions)\n",
    "3. Impute null `score` with 0 (player scored nothing — session ended abnormally)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 0,
   "metadata": {
    "application/vnd.databricks.v1+cell": {
     "cellMetadata": {"byteLimit": 2048000, "rowLimit": 10000},
     "inputWidgets": {},
     "nuid": "gp-s-007",
     "showTitle": false,
     "title": ""
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Count invalid records before cleaning\n",
    "invalid_duration = sessions_raw.filter(F.col(\"duration_minutes\") <= 0).count()\n",
    "null_scores      = sessions_raw.filter(F.col(\"score\").isNull()).count()\n",
    "log.info(\"Sessions: %d rows with invalid duration, %d rows with null score\",\n",
    "         invalid_duration, null_scores)\n",
    "\n",
    "sessions_silver = (\n",
    "    sessions_raw\n",
    "    .withColumn(\"session_date\",     F.to_date(F.col(\"session_date\"), \"yyyy-MM-dd\"))  # cast to date\n",
    "    .filter(F.col(\"duration_minutes\") > 0)                                            # drop invalid\n",
    "    .withColumn(\"score\", F.coalesce(F.col(\"score\"), F.lit(0)))                        # impute nulls\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "before = sessions_raw.count()\n",
    "after  = sessions_silver.count()\n",
    "print(f\"game_sessions: {before} → {after} rows  (dropped {before - after} invalid-duration records)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "null_report(sessions_silver, \"game_sessions_silver\")\n",
    "display(sessions_silver.limit(10))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 7. Clean `purchases` → Silver\n",
    "\n",
    "**Steps:**\n",
    "1. Standardize `category` with `initcap(lower())`\n",
    "2. Cast `purchase_date` from string to date\n",
    "3. Drop rows where `amount_spent` ≤ 0 (invalid / negative transactions)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 0,
   "metadata": {
    "application/vnd.databricks.v1+cell": {
     "cellMetadata": {"byteLimit": 2048000, "rowLimit": 10000},
     "inputWidgets": {},
     "nuid": "gp-s-008",
     "showTitle": false,
     "title": ""
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Count negative amounts before cleaning\n",
    "negative_amounts = purchases_raw.filter(F.col(\"amount_spent\") <= 0).count()\n",
    "log.info(\"Purchases: %d rows with invalid (negative) amount_spent\", negative_amounts)\n",
    "\n",
    "purchases_silver = (\n",
    "    purchases_raw\n",
    "    .withColumn(\"category\",      F.initcap(F.lower(F.col(\"category\"))))\n",
    "    .withColumn(\"purchase_date\", F.to_date(F.col(\"purchase_date\"), \"yyyy-MM-dd\"))\n",
    "    .filter(F.col(\"amount_spent\") > 0)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "before = purchases_raw.count()\n",
    "after  = purchases_silver.count()\n",
    "print(f\"purchases: {before} → {after} rows  (dropped {before - after} negative-amount records)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nDistinct category values (silver):\")\n",
    "display(purchases_silver.groupBy(\"category\").count().orderBy(\"category\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "null_report(purchases_silver, \"purchases_silver\")\n",
    "display(purchases_silver.limit(10))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 8. Write Silver Tables to Delta"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 0,
   "metadata": {
    "application/vnd.databricks.v1+cell": {
     "cellMetadata": {"byteLimit": 2048000, "rowLimit": 10000},
     "inputWidgets": {},
     "nuid": "gp-s-009",
     "showTitle": false,
     "title": ""
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "write_table(players_silver,   \"players_silver\")\n",
    "write_table(games_silver,     \"games_silver\")\n",
    "write_table(sessions_silver,  \"game_sessions_silver\")\n",
    "write_table(purchases_silver, \"purchases_silver\")\n",
    "\n",
    "log.info(\"All Silver tables written successfully.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
